.TH "mei_me_hbuf_write" 9 "mei_me_hbuf_write" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
mei_me_hbuf_write \- writes a message to host hw buffer.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" mei_me_hbuf_write
.BI "(struct mei_device *dev "  ","
.BI "const void *hdr "  ","
.BI "size_t hdr_len "  ","
.BI "const void *data "  ","
.BI "size_t data_len "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
the device structure
.IP "hdr" 12
header of message
.IP "hdr_len" 12
header length in bytes: must be multiplication of a slot (4bytes)
.IP "data" 12
payload
.IP "data_len" 12
payload length in bytes
.SH "RETURN"
0 if success, < 0 - otherwise.
